originalText.text:
My family recently solicited the services of “Rene Cargo Express”  for the first time unfortunately it will be the last time.

Reasons:

• When we called them to pick up our package they give exaggerated ETA’s (estimated time of arrival) for pick up.

• When package was delivered and arrived to the Dominican Republic it arrived in bad shape, half empty, many goods were stolen or damaged, the box was open when it arrived to the home of the receiver. After the fact! trying to reach them to complain had been to no avail, we try to call and call but no answer, (VERY UNPROFESSIONAL!)

• This company has limited liability and provided very poor service.

• We hope that they address the issue of what went wrong during the process of our shipment, and we hope that this does not happen to anyone else. We like others alike have families in dire need in the Dominican Republic and for essential goods such as: Clothes, foods, and medicines to be stolen is simply despicable! Should the goods have been stolen here in New York City, United States by Rene Express Cargo, in transit onboard the cargo vessel, or in the Dominican Republic... this matter should be investigated ASAP. (As Soon As Possible)

originalText.text: Family bussines providing shipping to Dominican Republic door to door service, great discounts. Free boxes when you ship with them. Very reasonable prices, super flexible on pick up time. Very professional team of father and son with over 25 Years experience in the shipping industry. If you call them and make an appointment they will bring you the boxes for free at your door. The pick up from Queens. Bronx, Brooklyn, Yankers, Long Island and a lot more. Give them a try. It will be the best desition you made. SUPPORT SMALL BUSSINES.
